<br>
No, it isn't a bad thing.  Defense skill goes up really slow. You need to work on it before you level up, on the weakest mobs you can find that are still dark blue.  I remember making a Warrior to serve as a scout/corpse puller in Kael.  I was totally untwinked and got a Skin buff from a Druid that was nearby.  I leveled up to level 3 in under 2 hours, but my defense wasn't that good.  I just let a rat beat on me, while AFK for about 30 mins.  I didn't care if I died, since I only gained from dying at that point.<br>
<br>
I noticed that defense could increase when the mob missed you totally.  I think it normally did that, actually.  So I guess it might be a bad thing if you're going up vs. level 6 stuff at level 3.  You're not going to get skill, since I doubt that mob will miss. I also bet you're not going to be able to kill those level 6 things so easily, since your offense is so low. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukalran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/20/02 12:00:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1803.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can Too much AC be bad??</span><hr size=1> Offensive/defensive skills aren't worth worrying about with your twinks!<br>
<br>
(lets all the people saying WHAT!!! simmer down)<br>
<br>
at lvl 28, head to Great Divide, dig your way in to Bloodmaw.  Fight him until your skills are maxed.  He'll be higher level than you, so all of your skills will go up.  His attack is fairly high, ac fairly low and he's perma-rooted so if you want the fight to stop... simply back away from him.  AND... he has like 32k hp, with a fair regen... so it's not like you'll accidentally kill him.  Hell, at lvl 54 it took me an hour to solo kill him.  After lvl 28, you spend enough time per level (even getting PL'd), that your skills go up adequately. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaezbwa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaezBwA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/20/02 6:42:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1803.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can Too much AC be bad??</span><hr size=1> Actually, I spent about 30 minutes on magelo(hell yeah I was bored) and found got to about 900 AC at level 1(with all items that it possible to loot at level 1, including yeli/tormax/AoW loot) I bet there is some stuff I missed too, cuz I had cobalt arms, and some other crap on. <br>
