<br>
About dying and losing all your good equipment... If that AC equipment had +HP on it, then I'd think anyone under level 6, xp hunting, would be close to invincible.  Considering that they're getting hit for 2 almost every time with the occasional bash/kick for 2 because of the AC.  Mobs don't double hit either.  They would virtually be regenerating almost all the damage they're taking.  If not, they would be regenerating it back while they're running around looking for more mobs, since they cleared out the whole area, being twinked and all.<br>
<br>
I quit my well equipped level 40 Warrior to change race, because of faction reasons and was painting the newbie area red.  Only time I've had a corpse rot was when I was an untwinked level 2 DE Necro and my power went out when I was fighting 2 firebeetles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uludoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ludoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 3:02:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1803.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can Too much AC be bad??</span><hr size=1> I dunno if it still works, but you used to be able to bring skills up fighting caster pets (mage/necro/sk,etc). Did they patch that? <br>
